
ðŸ”§ Functional Requirements

Settlement Date Tabs

Fetch settlement dates dynamically from
<https://cdn.india.deltaex.org/web/options/info>

Use each settlement_time as a tab header (e.g. 02 Nov 25, 03 Nov 25, etc.)

When user clicks a tab â†’ load the respective option chain (calls and puts).

Compact Option Chain Table

For selected date, fetch option data via:

GET /v2/products?contract_types=call_options,put_options&underlying_asset=BTC

Match settlement_time for the selected expiry.

Table columns:
CePrice | Strike | PePrice

Each row = one strike pair.

option chain table cells are clickable , so i can selecting multilple ce and pe symbols . later we get candlesticks of these selected symbols ,to build a combined chart candlestics with lightweight charts.

Combined Candlestick Chart Section

Next to the table, render a chart using Lightweight Charts.

Upper pane: combined option (straddle/strangle) candlesticks.

Lower pane: underlying BTC candlestick chart (mark or index price).

Use /v2/history/candles?symbol=<symbol>&resolution=1m for fetching OHLC data.

Combine selected option symbols by averaging (or summing) call + put candles.

Straddle/Strangle Calculation

Straddle: Price = (Call + Put) / 2

Strangle: allow user to pick two distant strikes, average/sum their OHLC data.

Support toggling between these via a small UI switch.

WebSocket Live Updates

Subscribe to candlestick_1m and mark_price channels using
wss://socket.india.delta.exchange

Update both chart panes in real-time.

UI Layout

Top: Date tabs.

Left: Compact option chain table.

Right: Combined candle chart (with BTC candle pane below).

Use TailwindCSS for clean design.

